            <p>Known worldwide amount Flamenco aficionados Estrella Morena of Madrid made her debut at the age of 16 as “bailaora” of flamenco at the famous Tablao LOS CANASTEROS of Manolo Caracol. At 16 she was also soloist at the Tablao TORRES BERMEJAS. Shortly thereafter, she made her debut as principal dancer at the great TEATRO DE LA ZARZUELA in Madrid, and later as principal dancer at the tablao DUENDE for a period of 2 years. Estrella began her training and choreography in 1969 at a very young age, at the same time she became principal dancer with the Great Antonio, where she received training from some of the best teachers and choreographers from Madrid, which today have become master teachers and choreographers with the National Ballet of Spain. In 1985 Estrella moved with her family to Miami where she established herself as an artist alongside her husband, Pepe de Malaga, and her son, Jose Moreno, where they have collectively performed successfully in some of the best flamenco tablaos in Miami. <a href="#">Complete Bio</a></p>
