            <h3>Pepe de Málaga</h3>
            <strong>(Flamenco Singer)</strong><br>
            <p>Born in Costa del Sol, Malaga, Pepe de Malaga moved to Madrid at a very young age where he debuted as a cataor in the tablao Las Brujas. During this time, he gained his stage name. He has since been associated with renowned flamenco figures such as Fosforito, Antonio Molina, Marife de Triana, Rafael Farina, Juanita Reina and Caracolillo. In 1964 and 1973, he won two First Place awards Del Cante Flamenco singing in the Saetas form. As the cataor for the Ballet of Antonio and Rafael de Cordova, he toured all over Europe with great success. Thereafter he joined the company of Estrella Morena as exclusive cataor and once again toured all over Spain, Asia, Europe, and the US. Since then, he has been presented at an honorary gala for the King and Queenof Spain at the Waldorf Astoria in New York, the Chamber of Commerce of Spain , and the Casa de Espana of New York, Carnegie Hall, Chateu Madrid, the Spanish Institute  Hunter College, and the Barbizon Plaza. He has completed lengthy seasons in the Miami, FL and in 1984 was featured in a special presentation honoring Placido Domingo for hi movie "Carmen.". Most recently he sang at the Lincoln Theater in Miami Beach for Estrella Morena with the New Worlds Symphony and the renowned flamenco artist Carmen Linares. He has also performed as a special guest artist for Bailes Ferrer Flamenco music and dance, Irene Rimer and Ballet Flamenco La Rosa.</p>
